commentPostTextItems.html: So, after Sri Lanka racked up 302, thanks to a fine fifth ODI hundred from Upul Tharanga, Bangladesh were always going to be under the gun. It was heartening to see that they didn't give in easily, though. They lost some early wickets, then Aftab Ahmed took the attack back to them but couldnt curb his enthusiasm. Saqibul Hasan hung around for a maiden ODI fifty, an unbeaten 67, but he was sluggish and couldnt really for the pace. In the end, Sri Lanka's spinners and medium pacers did a good job to restrict Bangladesh to 265.
Do check out S Rajesh's spiffing bulletin for an in-depth account of today's proceedings.

That's all we have for you this evening. I hope you've enjoyed our coverage of this match, the first of the 2006 Champions Trophy. Do join us tomorrow, Sunday, for the match between West Indies and Zimbabwe at Ahmedabad from 9.00 GMT (2.00pm IST). It will be myself, Jamie Alter, and Sriram Veera, to take you through the action. It's been a pleasure. Cheers, and good night!
